<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-20-1088 </DOCNO><TEXT>Examples are noted of evidence within the nuclear industry of the needfor integration of configuration management, power plant systems support,monitoring and trending, problem analysis and resolution, operationalsafety and regulatory compliance, life-cycle management, and technicalinformation dissemination and training. Strong site-based system engineerscan effectively address this need. Several utilities are currently implementingsuch programs. The purpose of this paper is to emphasize the benefitsof system engineers, to suggest some new ideas for system engineeringfunctions, and to present a survey of system engineering programs atnuclear utilities in the southeastern US.</TEXT></DOC>